100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 10, 1926, the British Parliament debated the controversial trade agreements with the Soviet Union, sparking intense discussions on international relations and economic policy. Meanwhile, in the United States, the ongoing aftermath of the Scopes Trial continued to influence public discourse on education and science. In the world of sports, the Winter Olympics were set to begin in Chamonix, France, showcasing the emergence of winter sports on the global stage.
